					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex. </support>
								<extent>131 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>295</height>
										<width>240</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>157</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>131 folios (+3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end of the manuscript). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>17 quires of mostly 8 leaves, marked with catchwords on the last page. </p>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.  </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>A number of pages are stained; ink (brown) is partly fading.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Visible pricking and ruling with brown ink. </p>
									<p>Jeremiah and Jonah open a new column. </p>
									<p>The chapters have been numbered with Hebrew letters. </p>
									<p>Masorah magna occupies two lines in the upper and three in the lower margin of each page. Omitted after folio 86. </p>
									<p>The beginning of the Hafterot is frequently marked in the margin. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary> Sefardi square script of  approximately 14th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Harleian binding. Harley gold stamp 'VIRTUTE ET FIDE' applied to the outside of the upper and lower covers.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
